WEBVTT

00:21.260 --> 00:25.820
Chapter 1 The Two Sisters

00:25.820 --> 00:34.060
It was the year 1757. The place was the dangerous

00:34.060 --> 00:36.860
and wild land west of the Hudson

00:36.860 --> 00:41.020
River. It was the third year of the war in

00:41.020 --> 00:44.580
North America. The war was between England

00:44.900 --> 00:51.460
and France. Each country wanted the land for itself. Indian

00:51.460 --> 00:53.620
tribes had always lived in

00:53.620 --> 00:58.160
that land. In the war, some tribes were fighting for

00:58.160 --> 01:01.160
the French. Other tribes were fighting

01:01.160 --> 01:06.820
for the English. Fort Edward was on the Hudson River.

01:08.080 --> 01:10.640
General Webb was the commander of the

01:10.640 --> 01:15.160
English army at Fort Edward. He was waiting for news

01:15.160 --> 01:19.320
of General Montcom. Montcom was the

01:19.320 --> 01:24.180
commander of the French army. The news came one morning.

01:25.140 --> 01:27.680
An Indian called Magua arrived.

01:29.240 --> 01:34.100
Montcom and the French army are coming towards Fort William

01:34.100 --> 01:36.820
Henry. Magua told General Webb.

01:38.220 --> 01:43.480
Fort William Henry was 15 miles away. It was at

01:43.480 --> 01:47.700
the south end of Lake Horican. How many

01:47.700 --> 01:53.060
men has Montcom got? Asked Webb. As many as the

01:53.060 --> 01:57.360
leaves on the trees said Magua. General Monroe

01:57.360 --> 02:04.300
wants more soldiers at Fort William Henry. I will send

02:04.300 --> 02:09.820
1500 men, said General Webb. General Monroe

02:09.820 --> 02:13.780
was the commander of the English army at Fort William

02:13.780 --> 02:16.200
Henry. He had two daughters,

02:16.800 --> 02:23.080
Cora and Alice. Cora was about 23 years old and

02:23.080 --> 02:29.020
Alice was 18. Cora had dark hair and a beautiful

02:29.020 --> 02:36.180
face. Alice had fair hair and blue eyes. These two

02:36.180 --> 02:39.620
young women were at Fort Edward but they were

02:39.620 --> 02:43.660
going to travel to Fort William Henry. They were going

02:43.660 --> 02:47.820
to meet their father. General Webb spoke

02:47.820 --> 02:53.120
to Cora and Alice. Magua knows a secret path through

02:53.120 --> 02:55.980
the forest, Sir General Webb. He will

02:55.980 --> 03:00.780
be your guide. Magua and Major Duncan Hayward will take

03:00.780 --> 03:05.240
you to Fort William Henry. Major Duncan

03:05.240 --> 03:09.880
Hayward was a young English officer. He and the two

03:09.880 --> 03:13.760
young women left Fort Edward. They rode on

03:13.760 --> 03:19.800
horses. Magua walked in front of them. Alice watched Magua.

03:20.560 --> 03:23.280
I don't like him Cora, she said.

03:23.780 --> 03:26.860
What do you think? Will we be safe in the

03:26.860 --> 03:32.880
forest with Magua? We must trust Magua, said Cora. The

03:32.880 --> 03:37.280
French know our soldiers' paths, said Duncan, but Magua's path

03:37.280 --> 03:40.560
is secret. He smiled at Alice

03:40.560 --> 03:45.280
and she smiled at him. Duncan Hayward was in love

03:45.280 --> 03:50.100
with Alice. Magua is a hero, said Duncan,

03:50.620 --> 03:54.680
but he lived with the Mohawks. The Mohawks are friends

03:54.680 --> 04:02.860
of the English. Magua came to us. Your

04:02.860 --> 04:06.620
father, then he said, but I don't remember all the

04:06.620 --> 04:10.620
story. Duncan knew more about Magua,

04:11.020 --> 04:15.020
but he did not tell Cora and Alice. He did

04:15.020 --> 04:19.220
not say, a few years ago, your father's men beat

04:19.220 --> 04:20.000
Magua.

04:20.520 --> 04:25.360
Now Magua hates your father. Duncan did not want to

04:25.360 --> 04:29.680
frighten the young women, so they followed Magua

04:29.680 --> 04:55.220
through the forest. Chapter 2. Lost in the Forest A

04:55.220 --> 04:57.060
few miles west of Fort Edward,

04:57.060 --> 05:01.280
three men were sitting near a river. Two of the

05:01.280 --> 05:04.680
men were Indians. The other was a white man.

05:06.140 --> 05:11.180
Chingaczguk and his son, Unkas, were Mohicans. The white man

05:11.180 --> 05:15.100
was a scout called Hawkeye. Hawkeye

05:15.100 --> 05:19.580
had a long hunting gun. The three men were talking.

05:20.680 --> 05:24.200
My tribe is the oldest Indian tribe,

05:24.200 --> 05:29.660
Chingaczguk said. The blood of the Mohican chiefs is in

05:29.660 --> 05:35.380
me. Many summers ago, my tribe came here to

05:35.380 --> 05:40.080
the land of the Delaware's. Where are the Mohicans now?

05:40.580 --> 05:53.820
asked Hawkeye. Where are the flowers of those

05:53.820 --> 05:59.640
last of the Mohicans? Suddenly they heard a noise. They

05:59.640 --> 06:02.840
turned quickly. Hawkeye lifted his gun.

06:03.840 --> 06:08.780
Who is it? He said. Duncan Hayward rode out of

06:08.780 --> 06:11.840
the forest. Cora and Alice followed him.

06:12.640 --> 06:16.700
I am an English officer, Duncan said. We have come

06:16.700 --> 06:20.500
from Fort Edward. How far is it to Fort William

06:20.500 --> 06:26.340
Henry? Hawkeye laughed. Fort William Henry, you are going the

06:26.340 --> 06:29.220
wrong way, he said. You are near

06:29.220 --> 06:35.340
Glen's Falls. The wrong way, said Duncan. Then we are

06:35.340 --> 06:39.200
lost. But our Indian guide, you have an

06:39.200 --> 06:42.860
Indian guide, but you are lost in the forest, said

06:42.860 --> 06:46.500
Hawkeye. That is very strange. Is he a

06:46.500 --> 06:51.540
Delaware? He is called Magua. He is a Huron, said

06:51.540 --> 06:54.860
Duncan. But he lives with the Mohawks, and he is

06:54.860 --> 06:54.960
a

06:54.960 --> 06:59.460
guide for the Inc., a Huron, said Hawkeye quickly. You

06:59.460 --> 07:09.140
can trust a Mohican or a Delaware, but you

07:09.920 --> 07:14.760
let me see him. Magua was standing behind Cora's horse.

07:15.700 --> 07:18.340
Hawkeye looked at him. Then he went and

07:18.340 --> 07:25.460
spoke to Chingachguk and Unkas. Magua moved quickly. He ran

07:25.460 --> 07:29.020
into the forest. Hawkeye, Chingachguk and

07:29.020 --> 07:35.100
Unkas ran after him. But Magua escaped. What can I

07:35.100 --> 07:39.400
do, thought Duncan? We are lost. He turned

07:39.400 --> 07:42.720
to Hawkeye. Will you take us to Fort William Henry?

07:43.260 --> 07:46.960
He asked. We will give you money. Hawkeye

07:46.960 --> 07:51.120
looked at Cora and Alice. We will take you, he

07:51.120 --> 07:55.630
told Duncan. Money is not important. We will not

07:55.630 --> 07:59.770
leave you and the two young women here. Magua and

07:59.770 --> 08:03.250
his Huron friends will find you. Come now,

08:03.570 --> 08:09.770
quickly. Duncan and Hawkeye spoke to Cora and Alice. The

08:09.770 --> 08:12.730
sisters got off their horses. The Mohicans

08:12.730 --> 08:17.550
took the animals away. They will hide the horses until

08:17.550 --> 08:21.730
the morning, said Hawkeye. He pulled a canoe

08:21.730 --> 08:24.810
from the tall grass at the side of the river.

08:25.610 --> 08:28.910
Get into the canoe, he said. We will go to

08:28.910 --> 08:29.430
a cave

08:29.970 --> 08:35.350
and we will stay there tonight. Duncan, Cora and Alice

08:35.350 --> 08:39.070
got into the canoe. Hawkeye pushed the

08:39.070 --> 08:42.110
canoe to the middle of the river. Then he got

08:42.110 --> 08:46.170
into the canoe. He started to paddle along the river.

08:46.970 --> 08:50.630
Soon they heard the sound of a great waterfall in

08:50.630 --> 08:55.030
front of them. Glens falls. A few minutes later,

08:55.570 --> 09:02.110
they saw the waterfall. Hawkeye paddled the canoe close to

09:02.110 --> 09:05.050
the great waterfall. Alice was afraid.

09:06.070 --> 09:10.010
She closed her eyes. Hawkeye stopped the canoe by a

09:10.010 --> 09:14.770
large, flat rock. Cora, Alice and Duncan got

09:14.770 --> 09:19.070
out of the canoe. Wait on the flat rock, Hawkeye

09:19.070 --> 09:21.430
said to them. I will bring the Mohicans.

09:23.190 --> 09:27.590
A few minutes later, Hawkeye came back with Chingotchgoof and

09:27.590 --> 09:30.410
Unkas. The scout led everybody

09:30.410 --> 09:35.570
to a cave behind the waterfall. The cave was deep

09:35.570 --> 09:41.110
and narrow and dark. Hawkeye immediately made a fire.

09:42.310 --> 09:48.130
Alice looked at the tall young Mohican, Unkas. A strong

09:48.130 --> 09:51.550
man is guarding us, she said quietly to her

09:51.550 --> 09:54.210
sister. We will be safe tonight.

10:16.250 --> 10:20.070
Chapter 3 The Fight at Glens Falls

10:23.390 --> 10:26.670
Hawkeye woke Duncan early the next morning.

10:27.550 --> 10:30.750
We must go, he said. I will get the canoe.

10:31.990 --> 10:35.630
Wake Miss Cora and Miss Alice, but do not make

10:35.630 --> 10:36.410
any noise.

10:37.610 --> 10:41.890
Duncan went to the back of the cave. Cora, Alice,

10:42.330 --> 10:44.230
he said quietly. Wake up.

10:45.590 --> 10:50.830
Suddenly there were shouts and cries outside. Duncan ran to

10:50.830 --> 10:53.350
the front of the cave. The sound

10:53.350 --> 10:57.410
of guns came from the forest. There were many Indians

10:57.410 --> 10:59.010
on the other side of the river.

10:59.990 --> 11:06.590
Turons thought Duncan. Then Duncan saw Hawkeye. The scout was

11:06.590 --> 11:08.090
shooting from the flat rock.

11:09.030 --> 11:14.050
Duncan saw a Huron fall into the rushing water. Then

11:14.050 --> 11:17.070
the other Hurons ran back into the forest.

11:18.310 --> 11:23.110
Hawkeye came back into the cave. They have gone, he

11:23.110 --> 11:24.990
said. Will they come back?

11:25.630 --> 11:31.190
Ask Duncan. Yes, they will come back, replied Hawkeye. Miss

11:31.190 --> 11:34.270
Cora and Miss Alice must stay here

11:34.270 --> 11:38.010
in the cave. We will go to the rocks and

11:38.010 --> 11:39.190
wait for the Hurons.

11:43.330 --> 11:49.450
Duncan, Hawkeye, Unkas, and Chingotchkook sat with their guns. They

11:49.450 --> 11:50.870
sat behind some rocks

11:50.870 --> 11:57.870
near the waterfall. They waited. Minutes passed. Then an hour

11:57.870 --> 11:58.450
passed.

12:01.610 --> 12:05.390
Suddenly they heard the wild cries of the Hurons again.

12:06.610 --> 12:09.330
Four Indians ran across the flat rock

12:09.330 --> 12:16.390
towards the cave. Chingotchkook and Unkas fired their guns. The

12:16.390 --> 12:18.490
first two Hurons fell to the ground.

12:20.010 --> 12:25.070
The third Huron jumped on Hawkeye. Each man had a

12:25.070 --> 12:28.770
knife. But Hawkeye was stronger than the Huron.

12:29.410 --> 12:34.870
He killed the Huron with his knife. The fourth Huron

12:34.870 --> 12:35.870
fought with Duncan.

12:37.230 --> 12:41.670
Unkas ran to help the officer. The young Mohican killed

12:41.670 --> 12:45.950
the Huron. Then Unkas and Duncan ran back

12:45.950 --> 12:49.950
to the rocks. The Hurons on the other side of

12:49.950 --> 12:51.810
the river started to shoot again.

12:53.230 --> 12:58.330
And Chingotchkook shot at them. The shooting went on and

12:58.330 --> 13:01.670
on. Rocks and trees near the cave

13:01.670 --> 13:06.470
were broken in a hundred places. But Hawkeye and his

13:06.470 --> 13:08.090
friends were not hurt.

13:08.990 --> 13:15.150
And Cora and Alice were safe in the cave. Hawkeye

13:15.150 --> 13:18.130
saw a Huron in a tree on the other side

13:18.130 --> 13:18.610
of the river.

13:19.590 --> 13:23.890
The scout lifted his long gun and fired. There was

13:23.890 --> 13:27.090
a cry and the Indian fell from the tree.

13:28.430 --> 13:31.330
I have no more bullets, said Hawkeye.

13:32.270 --> 13:36.210
Unkas go to the canoe. There are some bullets in

13:36.210 --> 13:36.470
the canoe.

13:37.850 --> 13:42.270
Unkas ran quickly across the flat rock. But he was

13:42.270 --> 13:46.490
too late. A Huron was pushing the canoe across the

13:46.490 --> 13:46.710
river.

13:50.890 --> 13:54.770
Duncan Hawkeye and the two Mohicans went back to the

13:54.770 --> 13:54.990
cave.

13:55.890 --> 14:01.010
What can we do now? asked Duncan. Hawkeye thought for

14:01.010 --> 14:01.550
a few minutes.

14:02.450 --> 14:06.510
There will be guards on the paths, he said. The

14:06.510 --> 14:10.430
Hurons will watch every path. We must swim.

14:11.310 --> 14:15.290
We must jump into the river. The rushing water will

14:15.290 --> 14:17.130
take us past the Hurons.

14:18.090 --> 14:20.870
The scout looked at Cora and Alice.

14:21.830 --> 14:26.950
We cannot swim, said Cora. Alice and I will stay

14:26.950 --> 14:27.410
here.

14:28.230 --> 14:32.890
Go to General Monroe at Fort William Henry. General Monroe

14:32.890 --> 14:34.690
must send soldiers.

14:36.830 --> 14:41.090
Chingaczuk, Unkas and Hawkeye talked quietly together.

14:42.410 --> 14:46.030
Then Chingaczuk ran out of the cave and jumped into

14:46.030 --> 14:46.430
the river.

14:47.130 --> 14:51.170
A moment later Hawkeye put down his long gun and

14:51.170 --> 14:52.370
followed Chingaczuk.

14:52.870 --> 14:55.510
The rushing water took them away.

14:58.050 --> 14:59.490
Cora looked at Unkas.

15:00.170 --> 15:01.830
Go with them, she said.

15:02.550 --> 15:04.970
I will stay, said the young Mohican.

15:05.490 --> 15:10.050
No, said Cora. Please, Unkas, go with them.

15:11.190 --> 15:15.150
Unkas was unhappy, but he jumped into the water too.

15:16.390 --> 15:17.530
Cora looked at Duncan.

15:18.450 --> 15:22.030
I am going to stay, said Duncan. He looked at

15:22.030 --> 15:24.530
Alice. I cannot leave you.

15:28.590 --> 15:31.750
There were shouts and cries from the Hurons on the

15:31.750 --> 15:32.230
flat rock.

15:32.990 --> 15:34.630
Duncan looked out of the cave.

15:35.830 --> 15:38.910
The Hurons were looking behind the rocks near the waterfall.

15:40.050 --> 15:43.710
They are looking for us, thought Duncan. He went quickly

15:43.710 --> 15:45.110
back into the cave.

15:45.990 --> 15:49.670
Our friends will bring help soon, he said to Cora

15:49.670 --> 15:50.150
and Alice.

15:51.330 --> 15:56.010
Cora was afraid. Her face was white. She cried out.

15:57.050 --> 15:57.430
Duncan turned

15:58.130 --> 16:01.010
and he saw the terrible face of Magua.

16:01.750 --> 16:06.790
Where are the Mohicans, asked Magua? Where is the scout,

16:07.370 --> 16:09.310
Hawkeye, the long gun?

16:10.650 --> 16:13.430
Suddenly the cave was full of Hurons.

16:14.310 --> 16:16.230
One of them picked up Hawkeye's gun.

16:17.010 --> 16:21.110
They have gone, said Duncan. They will bring help soon.

16:22.470 --> 16:26.370
The Hurons were angry. They were going to kill their

16:26.370 --> 16:26.650
prisoners,

16:27.730 --> 16:30.510
but Magua spoke to them quickly and quietly.

16:31.750 --> 16:36.310
Then the Hurons took Duncan, Cora, and Alice to the

16:36.310 --> 16:36.810
flat rock.

16:37.690 --> 16:39.570
One of the Hurons brought the canoe.

16:40.310 --> 16:43.970
Get into the canoe, Magua said.

16:45.130 --> 16:47.970
Duncan and the sisters got into the canoe.

16:49.050 --> 16:52.310
Magua and the Hurons took them across the river.

16:53.530 --> 16:56.090
The prisoners got out of the canoe on the other

16:56.090 --> 16:57.150
side of the river.

16:58.170 --> 17:01.010
Magua and five Hurons stayed with them.

17:01.830 --> 17:05.170
The other Hurons walked away into the forest.

