41:53.150 --> 41:56.570
At the bottom of the mountain, the fog was very

41:56.570 --> 41:56.950
thick.

41:57.590 --> 41:59.650
Be careful, said Hawkeye.

42:00.230 --> 42:02.930
There are many French soldiers along this path.

42:03.650 --> 42:04.970
Walk quietly.

42:06.430 --> 42:08.090
They followed him through the fog.

42:09.110 --> 42:10.610
Suddenly they heard voices.

42:11.490 --> 42:12.630
Who is there?

42:13.190 --> 42:14.310
Said a soldier in French.

42:15.570 --> 42:17.410
Duncan replied in French.

42:18.310 --> 42:20.750
A friend of France, he said.

42:21.710 --> 42:24.090
Who are you, shouted the Frenchmen.

42:24.850 --> 42:28.310
But Duncan and his friends walked away quickly.

42:29.230 --> 42:31.010
They went on through the fog.

42:31.890 --> 42:35.090
At last they arrived at the walls of the fort.

42:36.190 --> 42:39.410
An English voice shouted from the top of the wall.

42:40.230 --> 42:41.130
The French are here.

42:41.690 --> 42:42.590
Shoot, shoot.

42:43.990 --> 42:45.310
Father, Father!

42:45.670 --> 42:46.090
Ah, they shouted.

42:46.650 --> 42:47.110
It is us.

42:47.810 --> 42:48.410
Save your daughters.

42:49.250 --> 42:50.350
Don't shoot men.

42:50.870 --> 42:52.030
Said the voice of General Monroe.

42:52.770 --> 42:53.830
My daughters are here.

42:54.110 --> 42:54.930
Open the gates.

42:56.150 --> 42:57.390
The gates opened.

42:58.210 --> 42:59.850
Soldiers came out of the fort.

43:00.770 --> 43:02.290
They took everybody inside.

43:03.070 --> 43:06.930
Duncan, the young women, Hawkeye, and the Mohicans.

43:08.110 --> 43:12.190
But everybody in Fort William Henry was in danger.

43:34.450 --> 43:39.230
The French army fired their big guns at Fort William

43:39.230 --> 43:39.550
Henry.

43:40.590 --> 43:42.710
Many English soldiers were killed.

43:44.330 --> 43:45.430
General Monroe waited.

43:46.390 --> 43:49.490
But General Webb did not send any soldiers.

43:50.950 --> 43:54.150
Monroe sent Hawkeye to Fort Edward with a message.

43:55.270 --> 43:58.410
General Webb gave Hawkeye a letter for Monroe.

43:59.510 --> 44:02.490
The scout started to go back to Fort William Henry.

44:03.490 --> 44:05.410
But French soldiers stopped him.

44:06.250 --> 44:07.510
They took the letter.

44:08.450 --> 44:10.750
They tied Hawkeye's hands with rope.

44:10.750 --> 44:16.230
The next morning Duncan Hayward was standing by the gates

44:16.230 --> 44:17.750
of Fort William Henry.

44:18.610 --> 44:21.630
He saw three men coming towards the fort.

44:22.510 --> 44:23.650
He went to General Monroe.

44:24.550 --> 44:26.330
General Monroe, he said,

44:26.930 --> 44:29.630
two French soldiers are at the gates of the fort.

44:30.290 --> 44:31.550
Hawkeye is with them.

44:32.290 --> 44:34.250
But when will help come from Fort Edward?

44:35.890 --> 44:38.470
Hawkeye came into General Monroe's room.

44:39.470 --> 44:42.470
General Webb gave me a letter for you, he said.

44:43.230 --> 44:44.810
But the French soldiers took it.

44:45.630 --> 44:47.830
General Montkam wants to speak to you.

44:48.350 --> 44:49.750
You must go to his camp.

44:52.430 --> 44:56.310
A French officer met Monroe and Duncan at the gates

44:56.310 --> 44:57.010
of the fort.

44:57.950 --> 45:01.230
They went to General Montkam's tent in the French camp.

45:02.070 --> 45:05.690
There were French officers and Indian chiefs in the tent.

45:06.350 --> 45:08.430
Then Duncan saw Magua.

45:09.310 --> 45:11.710
Magua was fighting for the French.

45:12.910 --> 45:15.730
The Huron looked at Duncan and smiled.

45:17.590 --> 45:19.150
Montkam spoke first.

45:19.950 --> 45:20.770
He spoke to Monroe.

45:21.970 --> 45:24.670
You have fought well, General, he said.

45:25.450 --> 45:27.510
But now you must stop fighting.

45:28.750 --> 45:30.630
Montkam gave a letter to Monroe.

45:31.910 --> 45:32.870
Montkam read it quickly.

45:33.970 --> 45:35.190
Then he gave it to Duncan.

45:36.180 --> 45:38.310
The letter was from General Webb.

45:39.350 --> 45:40.110
The letter said,

45:41.010 --> 45:43.470
We cannot send any more men.

45:44.370 --> 45:47.790
The Indians have killed too many of my soldiers.

45:49.270 --> 45:50.910
Monroe looked at Duncan.

45:52.130 --> 45:53.110
They did not speak.

45:54.570 --> 45:56.730
Then General Montkam spoke to Monroe.

45:57.830 --> 46:02.090
You and your soldiers must leave thought William Henry, he

46:02.090 --> 46:02.290
said.

46:02.810 --> 46:06.490
You can take your guns, but do not take your

46:06.490 --> 46:06.770
bullets.

46:07.810 --> 46:13.030
Your men, women and children will be safe, but we

46:13.030 --> 46:14.650
will burn the fort.

46:16.050 --> 46:17.970
General Monroe was unhappy.

46:18.930 --> 46:21.110
We will leave in the morning, he said.

46:21.950 --> 46:25.030
Then he and Duncan went back to the fort.

46:26.510 --> 46:27.810
Magua was angry.

46:27.810 --> 46:30.150
He spoke to the Huron chiefs.

46:30.870 --> 46:33.030
The English will leave the fort.

46:33.910 --> 46:35.670
The French will not kill them.

46:36.450 --> 46:39.470
But the English are the enemies of the Hurons.

46:40.210 --> 46:42.150
We will kill the English.

46:44.550 --> 46:50.670
3,000 English people, soldiers, women and children, left the

46:50.670 --> 46:50.910
fort.

46:51.870 --> 46:55.850
They walked past the French soldiers and they walked towards

46:55.850 --> 46:56.530
the forest.

46:57.810 --> 47:01.590
The English soldiers carried their guns, but they had no

47:01.590 --> 47:01.990
bullets.

47:07.430 --> 47:10.670
Magua and the Hurons were standing in the forest.

47:11.650 --> 47:13.370
They watched Fort William Henry.

47:14.510 --> 47:18.090
The English left the fort and walked into the forest.

47:19.370 --> 47:22.950
Then 2,000 Indians attacked.

47:24.490 --> 47:26.270
The English could not fight.

47:26.270 --> 47:29.030
They had no bullets in their guns.

47:30.130 --> 47:32.650
Many of the English were killed.

47:34.170 --> 47:36.350
Alice and Cora saw their father.

47:37.150 --> 47:39.230
He was running towards the French camp.

47:40.010 --> 47:41.630
He was going to find Munkam.

47:42.310 --> 47:44.050
He was going to ask for help.

47:44.770 --> 47:46.470
Father, Father!

47:46.810 --> 47:48.690
Shouted Alice, we are here.

47:50.050 --> 47:51.890
But Monroe did not hear them.

47:52.510 --> 47:53.610
He did not stop.

47:54.870 --> 47:56.190
Magua was watching.

47:56.850 --> 47:58.170
He ran to Cora.

47:58.570 --> 48:00.450
Will you come with me now?

48:00.910 --> 48:03.130
He said, never said Cora.

48:03.430 --> 48:05.230
I will not be your wife.

48:06.590 --> 48:07.930
The Huron looked at her.

48:08.690 --> 48:09.750
But he did not speak.

48:10.690 --> 48:12.150
Then he turned to Alice.

48:12.930 --> 48:14.370
He held Alice's arms.

48:15.030 --> 48:16.690
He pulled her towards a horse.

48:17.470 --> 48:18.930
Stop, shouted Cora.

48:19.290 --> 48:20.550
Then she ran after them.

48:21.830 --> 48:23.730
Magua put Alice on the horse.

48:24.910 --> 48:26.710
Then he put Cora on the horse too.

48:27.770 --> 48:29.490
The Huron took them along a path.

48:30.170 --> 48:31.190
Towards Lake Horakon.

48:57.190 --> 49:01.330
The Huron took them along a path.

49:01.330 --> 49:02.770
Chapter 7

49:03.670 --> 49:04.270
The Trail

49:06.010 --> 49:07.690
Three days had passed.

49:08.790 --> 49:11.190
Fort William Henry had burnt down.

49:12.070 --> 49:13.730
The French soldiers had gone.

49:14.250 --> 49:15.970
The Indians had gone.

49:16.810 --> 49:19.230
The bodies of many English soldiers,

49:19.230 --> 49:22.210
soldiers, women and children lay on the ground.

49:24.150 --> 49:29.110
In the evening five men walked through the forest, Monroe,

49:30.490 --> 49:32.410
Duncan, Hawkeye, Chingacchkuk,

49:32.890 --> 49:35.150
and Unkis were looking for Kora and Alice.

49:36.130 --> 49:39.150
They found the dead bodies of many English people.

49:40.130 --> 49:43.450
The five men were sad and angry.

49:44.530 --> 49:47.610
Suddenly Unkis shouted to the others, look!

49:47.610 --> 49:51.210
He had a small piece of cloth in his hand.

49:52.210 --> 49:54.970
That is a piece of Kora's dress, said Monroe.

49:56.290 --> 49:59.510
Unkis found footprints on the ground near a tree.

50:00.250 --> 50:03.770
Three people and a horse have stood here, he said.

50:04.790 --> 50:09.310
Then Chingacchkuk found Alice's necklace, and he found another piece

50:09.310 --> 50:10.250
of Kora's dress.

50:11.150 --> 50:17.150
Duncan took the necklace, he smiled, Alice is alive, he

50:17.150 --> 50:17.390
said.

50:18.130 --> 50:21.170
Miss Kora has left a trail, said Hawkeye.

50:21.930 --> 50:23.930
She has left pieces of her dress.

50:24.710 --> 50:28.630
We can follow this trail, but we must go quietly.

50:29.530 --> 50:30.890
Magua is with them.

50:31.550 --> 50:33.750
But it is late, said Hawkeye.

50:34.370 --> 50:35.590
We will eat some food.

50:36.370 --> 50:37.930
We will sleep here tonight.

50:38.610 --> 50:41.470
Tomorrow we will follow Miss Kora's trail.

50:44.210 --> 50:48.690
Very early the next morning, Hawkeye woke the English officers

50:48.690 --> 50:49.690
and the Mohicans.

50:50.630 --> 50:52.970
The five men followed Kora's trail.

50:53.790 --> 50:55.590
It led them to Lake Horakin.

50:57.730 --> 51:01.490
Unkis and Chingacchkuk found a canoe in the grass near

51:01.490 --> 51:01.890
the lake.

51:02.810 --> 51:05.130
The five men got into the canoe.

51:05.130 --> 51:08.490
The Mohicans paddled it along the lake.

51:09.530 --> 51:12.510
After half an hour, Unkis spoke quietly.

51:13.230 --> 51:14.710
Smoke, he said.

51:15.390 --> 51:18.130
He was looking at a small island in front of

51:18.130 --> 51:18.290
them.

51:18.850 --> 51:21.370
Smoke from a fire, said Hawkeye.

51:22.070 --> 51:23.770
And there are two canoes.

51:25.410 --> 51:28.730
Suddenly some heurons ran from the trees on the island.

51:29.290 --> 51:30.890
They got into the two canoes.

51:31.790 --> 51:33.470
They are following us, said Duncan.

51:33.910 --> 51:34.690
Paddle faster!

51:35.570 --> 51:38.890
No, stop paddling, Chingacchkuk, said Hawkeye.

51:39.250 --> 51:40.090
I will shoot them.

51:40.790 --> 51:42.590
And he lifted his long gun.

51:43.670 --> 51:44.290
He fired.

51:45.990 --> 51:48.750
A heuron in the first canoe fell into the lake.

51:49.730 --> 51:51.610
The heurons stopped their two canoes.

51:52.450 --> 51:53.590
They did not follow.

51:55.170 --> 51:57.830
Chingacchkuk and Unkis started paddling again.

51:58.520 --> 52:00.450
The five men went on.

52:01.190 --> 52:03.070
They went north up the lake.

52:15.690 --> 52:16.190
Chapter 8.

52:17.090 --> 52:17.790
The Medicine Man.

52:19.150 --> 52:23.330
In the evening, the five men arrived at the north

52:23.330 --> 52:24.850
end of Lake Horrikan.

52:25.730 --> 52:26.910
They got out of the canoe.

52:27.870 --> 52:30.070
And Unkis and Chingacchkuk carried it.

52:30.710 --> 52:32.270
They put it under some trees.

52:33.410 --> 52:36.030
We have lost the trail, said Duncan.

52:36.530 --> 52:37.730
Where shall we go?

52:38.890 --> 52:42.350
My Mohican friends know the path to the heurons village,

52:42.730 --> 52:43.450
said Hawkeye.

52:44.110 --> 52:45.630
It is north of this place.

52:46.410 --> 52:48.430
That is where Magua is going.

52:49.290 --> 52:50.790
We will go north too.

52:53.530 --> 52:56.410
For two days, the men followed the path.

52:57.450 --> 52:58.910
They walked many miles.

52:59.950 --> 53:03.210
They arrived at the heurons village on the second day.

53:04.110 --> 53:05.410
It was early evening.

53:06.490 --> 53:09.710
There were about a hundred houses by a small lake.

53:12.990 --> 53:15.790
Hawkeye spoke to Chingacchkuk and Unkis.

53:16.630 --> 53:18.630
Then he spoke to Duncan and Monroe.

53:18.630 --> 53:23.850
General Monroe, stay with Chingacchkuk, said Hawkeye.

53:24.570 --> 53:25.650
Stay in the forest.

53:26.690 --> 53:28.970
Duncan and I will go into the village.

53:29.930 --> 53:32.270
Unkis, go up the hill to the west.

53:33.350 --> 53:34.170
Watch the village.

53:35.130 --> 53:35.910
Come back quickly.

53:36.930 --> 53:38.170
Tell us about the guards.

53:40.390 --> 53:41.830
An hour passed.

53:42.870 --> 53:44.050
The four men waited.

53:45.190 --> 53:47.290
Unkis did not come back.

53:48.530 --> 53:49.990
Suddenly Duncan spoke.

53:50.910 --> 53:52.450
I have a plan, he said.

53:53.090 --> 53:54.970
Hawkeye, give me your coat.

53:55.870 --> 53:58.670
I must not wear my red soldier's coat in the

53:58.670 --> 53:58.890
village.

53:59.470 --> 54:02.530
I will be a medicine man, a French doctor.

54:03.310 --> 54:04.430
I will speak French.

54:05.330 --> 54:08.590
I will walk through the village and go into the

54:08.590 --> 54:08.890
houses.

54:10.010 --> 54:12.870
The heurons will not hurt a medicine man.

54:12.870 --> 54:16.210
I will find Alice and Cora.

54:17.510 --> 54:19.850
It was a dangerous plan.

54:21.130 --> 54:23.550
Duncan put on Hawkeye's coat.

54:24.470 --> 54:26.690
Then he walked into the heurons village.

54:27.510 --> 54:30.630
There was a large wooden building in front of him.

54:31.390 --> 54:33.770
It was the meeting house of the heuron chiefs.

54:34.870 --> 54:36.270
Duncan went inside.

54:37.590 --> 54:40.810
Some heuron chiefs were sitting together.

54:40.810 --> 54:43.410
They saw Duncan come in.

54:44.250 --> 54:46.450
One of the chiefs walked forward.

54:47.190 --> 54:50.830
His hair was gray and he was tall and strong.

54:51.670 --> 54:54.690
He spoke to Duncan in the heuron language,

54:55.170 --> 54:57.070
but Duncan did not understand.

54:58.130 --> 54:59.790
Do you speak French?

55:00.490 --> 55:01.170
Duncan asked.

55:02.090 --> 55:03.750
The heuron replied in French.

55:04.850 --> 55:06.270
Why are you here?

55:06.650 --> 55:06.950
He asked.

55:07.710 --> 55:10.490
I am a medicine man, said Duncan.

55:11.210 --> 55:13.210
The king of France sent me.

55:13.790 --> 55:15.510
Are any heurons ill?

55:17.110 --> 55:19.970
Suddenly there were loud cries from the forest.

55:21.090 --> 55:23.210
The chiefs left the meeting house.

55:24.090 --> 55:25.130
Duncan followed them.

55:26.050 --> 55:28.230
More heurons were coming into the village.

55:28.990 --> 55:30.890
There was a prisoner in front of them.

55:31.650 --> 55:32.750
It was Uncas.

55:47.730 --> 55:50.230
In the heurons village.

55:52.310 --> 55:54.490
Uncas was not afraid.

55:55.730 --> 55:57.490
The heurons ran around him.

55:58.210 --> 55:58.450
They shouted.

55:59.530 --> 56:01.430
They pulled him towards the wooden building.

56:01.430 --> 56:05.190
Uncas saw Duncan outside the building.

56:06.310 --> 56:08.330
Hawkeye is safe, Uncas.

56:08.750 --> 56:09.790
Duncan said quietly.

56:11.150 --> 56:14.190
Then the heurons took Uncas into the meeting house.

56:15.390 --> 56:17.390
Duncan walked through the village.

56:18.210 --> 56:19.270
He looked in the houses.

56:20.290 --> 56:21.570
Nobody stopped him.

56:22.450 --> 56:24.230
Nobody asked any questions.

56:25.490 --> 56:28.730
But Duncan did not find Alice and Cora.

56:29.450 --> 56:31.750
He went back to the meeting house.

56:32.650 --> 56:33.450
He went inside.

56:34.550 --> 56:37.490
Uncas was standing and the chiefs were sitting.

56:38.650 --> 56:40.070
Duncan sat down too.

56:40.910 --> 56:42.370
He sat near the wall.

56:43.770 --> 56:46.170
Then another heuron came into the building.

56:47.090 --> 56:47.910
It was Magua.

56:49.090 --> 56:50.990
Magua did not see Duncan.

56:52.090 --> 56:53.130
But he saw Uncas.

56:53.990 --> 56:54.410
He shouted.

56:58.930 --> 57:00.370
Magua was angry.

57:01.330 --> 57:02.470
He turned to the chiefs.

57:03.430 --> 57:06.570
Many heurons died at Glen's Falls.

57:07.250 --> 57:07.490
He said.

57:08.530 --> 57:11.030
This Mohican is our enemy.

57:12.690 --> 57:17.130
Magua and two heurons took the young Mohican out of

57:17.130 --> 57:17.750
the meeting house.

57:19.110 --> 57:21.430
Then one of the chiefs spoke to Duncan.

57:22.490 --> 57:26.530
Medicine man, the wife of one of my men is

57:26.530 --> 57:26.870
ill.

57:27.550 --> 57:28.490
She is sick.

57:29.450 --> 57:31.150
Can you make her well?

57:32.250 --> 57:34.970
Take me to the woman, said Duncan.

57:36.270 --> 57:39.170
He followed the chief out of the meeting house.

57:39.950 --> 57:41.590
They went towards a hill.

57:42.350 --> 57:44.570
There was a cave in the hill.

57:45.730 --> 57:48.490
Duncan saw a bear following them.

57:49.190 --> 57:50.430
But he was not afraid.

57:52.270 --> 57:53.230
Indians liked bears.

57:54.250 --> 57:56.390
They often had bears in their villages.

57:58.170 --> 58:01.110
Duncan followed the chief into the cave.

58:02.010 --> 58:05.910
The cave was large and there were many rooms with

58:05.910 --> 58:06.850
stone walls.

58:08.010 --> 58:11.390
The chief took Duncan into one room.

58:12.490 --> 58:14.870
The sick woman was lying on the ground.

58:14.870 --> 58:17.610
Some other women were with her.

58:18.650 --> 58:20.210
Duncan looked at the sick woman.

58:21.110 --> 58:23.610
She is dying, he thought.

58:27.130 --> 58:30.730
The heuron chief waited and looked at Duncan.

58:31.810 --> 58:33.950
Duncan turned to the heuron chief.

58:34.670 --> 58:38.610
I must look at this sick woman alone, he said.

58:39.350 --> 58:40.630
My medicine is secret.

58:41.430 --> 58:43.630
Go with these four women.

58:44.450 --> 58:45.170
Wait outside.

58:46.790 --> 58:50.890
The chief and the four women left the cave.

58:52.350 --> 58:56.110
A few minutes later, the bear came into the cave.

58:57.170 --> 58:58.810
The bear made a loud noise.

59:01.590 --> 59:03.310
Duncan looked at the bear.

59:04.090 --> 59:06.550
Again, the bear made a loud noise.

59:06.550 --> 59:09.010
It walked towards Duncan.

59:09.930 --> 59:11.890
Suddenly it took off its head.

59:12.650 --> 59:13.810
It was Hawkeye.

59:14.610 --> 59:17.890
Hawkeye was wearing a bear's skin.

59:18.670 --> 59:20.810
What? said Duncan.

59:21.570 --> 59:22.170
Then he laughed.

59:22.910 --> 59:25.130
Why are you wearing a bear's skin?

59:25.710 --> 59:26.150
He asked.

59:27.050 --> 59:30.290
I found the bear's skin in a heuron's house.

59:30.630 --> 59:31.150
Said Hawkeye.

59:31.810 --> 59:33.870
Now the heurons will not stop me.

59:33.870 --> 59:37.130
But tell me, where is Miss Alice?

59:38.170 --> 59:39.590
I have been unlucky.

59:40.590 --> 59:43.550
I have not found Alice or Cora.

59:44.350 --> 59:46.730
And Unca's is a prisoner of the heurons.

59:48.270 --> 59:51.350
Magua has taken Miss Cora to the village of the

59:51.350 --> 59:52.970
Delaware's, said Hawkeye.

59:53.830 --> 59:56.570
I heard two heurons talking about her.

59:57.550 --> 01:00:00.750
Chingatchgook and Monroe are safe in the forest.

01:00:02.150 --> 01:00:03.970
Then Hawkeye heard a noise.

01:00:04.870 --> 01:00:06.330
He looked over a stone wall.

01:00:07.250 --> 01:00:10.170
Miss Alice is in the next room, he said.

01:00:11.210 --> 01:00:13.190
Duncan went into the next room.

01:00:14.050 --> 01:00:17.790
There were some blankets, cloths and animal skins in the

01:00:17.790 --> 01:00:18.010
room.

01:00:18.910 --> 01:00:20.010
And there was Alice.

01:00:21.050 --> 01:00:23.410
Her hands and feet were tied with rope.

01:00:24.310 --> 01:00:25.630
Her face was white.

01:00:26.570 --> 01:00:27.390
She was afraid.

01:00:28.230 --> 01:00:31.190
Duncan, she said, you are here.

01:00:31.930 --> 01:00:33.430
Yes, said Duncan.

01:00:34.310 --> 01:00:36.070
The untied her hands and feet.

01:00:36.650 --> 01:00:37.810
Where is Cora?

01:00:38.410 --> 01:00:38.870
Asked Alice.

01:00:39.410 --> 01:00:40.610
Where is my father?

01:00:41.370 --> 01:00:42.990
Your father is safe.

01:00:43.850 --> 01:00:46.210
He is with Chingatchgook, said Duncan.

01:00:46.590 --> 01:00:47.530
And Cora?

01:00:48.370 --> 01:00:48.990
Alice asked again.

01:00:49.590 --> 01:00:51.110
She is near here.

01:00:51.850 --> 01:00:54.130
She is at another village, said Duncan.

01:00:54.130 --> 01:00:56.670
She is with the Delaware's.

01:00:57.550 --> 01:01:00.730
Suddenly, somebody came into the room.

01:01:01.890 --> 01:01:02.950
It was Magua.

01:01:24.130 --> 01:01:26.770
Chapter 10, The Bear.

01:01:28.170 --> 01:01:30.610
Magua looked at Duncan and Alice.

01:01:31.490 --> 01:01:33.650
He laughed and went towards them.

01:01:34.430 --> 01:01:36.630
Suddenly the bear was in the room.

01:01:37.350 --> 01:01:38.950
It quickly held Magua.

01:01:39.610 --> 01:01:41.110
Magua could not move.

01:01:41.930 --> 01:01:43.570
He could not turn round.

01:01:44.630 --> 01:01:46.470
Duncan ran to the Huron.

01:01:47.010 --> 01:01:48.810
He tied Magua's arms.

01:01:49.730 --> 01:01:51.490
Then he tied Magua's feet.

01:01:52.510 --> 01:01:53.950
Magua started to speak.

01:01:54.830 --> 01:01:57.530
But Duncan put a cloth into his mouth.

01:01:59.030 --> 01:02:01.110
Hawkeye took off the bear's head.

01:02:01.850 --> 01:02:03.850
We must go quickly, he said.

01:02:04.450 --> 01:02:06.330
Alice, you will wear a blanket.

01:02:07.270 --> 01:02:09.290
You will be the sick Huron woman.

01:02:10.150 --> 01:02:12.290
Then you can leave the Huron's village.

01:02:13.950 --> 01:02:16.110
Hawkeye put on the bear's head again.

01:02:17.110 --> 01:02:19.510
Alice put a blanket over her head.

01:02:20.410 --> 01:02:22.890
Duncan carried Alice out of the cave.

01:02:23.650 --> 01:02:25.310
And Hawkeye followed Duncan.

01:02:27.390 --> 01:02:30.510
The Huron chief was outside the cave.

01:02:31.250 --> 01:02:35.050
I am taking the sick woman away, said Duncan.

01:02:35.830 --> 01:02:37.870
I will bring her to your house tomorrow.

01:02:39.530 --> 01:02:43.250
Hawkeye, Duncan and Alice left the village.

01:02:44.210 --> 01:02:47.550
Then Hawkeye led Duncan and Alice to a path.

01:02:48.290 --> 01:02:51.530
This path goes to a small river.

01:02:52.170 --> 01:02:53.130
Hawkeye said to them.

01:02:53.690 --> 01:02:55.190
You will see a hill.

01:02:55.950 --> 01:02:59.250
The village of the Delaware's is near the hill.

01:02:59.930 --> 01:03:02.250
You will be safe with the Delaware's.

01:03:02.950 --> 01:03:04.730
What are you going to do?

01:03:05.370 --> 01:03:05.950
Asked Duncan.

01:03:06.790 --> 01:03:09.910
I must go back for UNKAS, said Hawkeye.

01:03:12.590 --> 01:03:14.410
It was dark in the village.

01:03:14.410 --> 01:03:17.030
The Huron's were in their houses.

01:03:18.030 --> 01:03:18.670
They were asleep.

01:03:20.090 --> 01:03:22.030
Hawkeye was looking for UNKAS.

01:03:22.910 --> 01:03:25.210
The scout was wearing the bear's skin.

01:03:26.150 --> 01:03:28.070
He looked in all the buildings.

01:03:29.310 --> 01:03:32.070
Then he saw two men outside a house.

01:03:32.970 --> 01:03:35.770
They were guards, but they were asleep.

01:03:36.990 --> 01:03:40.130
Hawkeye quietly went inside the house.

01:03:41.470 --> 01:03:43.730
UNKAS was lying on the floor.

01:03:44.570 --> 01:03:47.010
His hands and feet were tied with rope.

01:03:48.370 --> 01:03:50.190
Hawkeye took off the bear's head.

01:03:51.170 --> 01:03:51.870
UNKAS smiled.

01:03:52.970 --> 01:03:55.110
Hawkeye, he said quietly.

01:03:58.090 --> 01:04:01.290
Hawkeye untied UNKAS's hands and feet.

01:04:02.350 --> 01:04:04.470
Then he took off the bear's skin.

01:04:05.330 --> 01:04:08.890
UNKAS and Hawkeye ran quickly from the village.

01:04:09.770 --> 01:04:13.230
We shall go to the Delaware's village, said Hawkeye.

01:04:13.830 --> 01:04:15.310
Yes, said UNKAS.

01:04:15.710 --> 01:04:18.450
The Delaware's are the children of my grandfather.

01:04:19.270 --> 01:04:20.430
They will help us.

01:04:22.250 --> 01:04:26.170
The next morning, the Huron's went to get UNKAS.

01:04:26.750 --> 01:04:28.290
They were going to kill him.

01:04:28.710 --> 01:04:30.870
They found the bear's skin.

01:04:31.510 --> 01:04:33.870
But they did not find the Mohican.

01:04:34.970 --> 01:04:36.570
Then they went to the cave.

01:04:37.490 --> 01:04:38.990
They found a dead woman.

01:04:39.710 --> 01:04:41.470
But they did not find Alice.

01:04:42.390 --> 01:04:43.830
They found Magua.

01:04:44.530 --> 01:04:46.310
His hands and feet were tied.

01:04:47.050 --> 01:04:48.550
A cloth was in his mouth.

01:04:49.930 --> 01:04:52.630
The Huron's untied Magua's hands and feet.

01:04:53.210 --> 01:04:55.150
They took the cloth from his mouth.

01:04:56.210 --> 01:04:57.270
Magua was angry.

01:04:58.250 --> 01:04:59.750
Kill the Mohican prisoner.

01:05:00.250 --> 01:05:00.350
No!

01:05:00.950 --> 01:05:01.270
He shouted.

01:05:02.030 --> 01:05:04.150
He has gone, said one of the chiefs.

01:05:05.130 --> 01:05:06.530
Magua shouted with anger.

01:05:07.450 --> 01:05:08.870
And he ran out of the cave.

01:05:16.430 --> 01:05:17.570
Chapter 11.

01:05:18.630 --> 01:05:19.550
The Old Chief.

01:05:22.170 --> 01:05:24.490
Magua went to the Delaware's village.

01:05:25.430 --> 01:05:28.090
The Delaware's were friends of France.

01:05:28.890 --> 01:05:30.850
But they did not fight in the war.

01:05:32.150 --> 01:05:34.590
Magua went to the Delaware's meeting house.

01:05:35.350 --> 01:05:37.330
The Delaware chiefs were talking.

01:05:38.150 --> 01:05:41.590
The Huron chief is welcome, said a Delaware.

01:05:42.210 --> 01:05:44.870
Is my woman prisoner safe and well?

01:05:45.330 --> 01:05:46.110
Asked Magua.

01:05:46.690 --> 01:05:48.510
She is well, said the Delaware.

01:05:49.230 --> 01:05:52.270
Then Magua said, are there strangers in the forest?

01:05:52.270 --> 01:05:53.250
White men?

01:05:54.570 --> 01:05:57.770
There are strangers in the village, said the Delaware.

01:05:58.330 --> 01:06:00.070
They are in my house.

01:06:00.910 --> 01:06:04.210
But strangers are always welcome in this village.

01:06:05.030 --> 01:06:08.210
What will the King of France say about this?

01:06:08.750 --> 01:06:09.270
Said Magua.

01:06:09.890 --> 01:06:13.810
His greatest enemy is here in the Delaware's village.

01:06:14.550 --> 01:06:16.930
This enemy is a white man.

01:06:17.610 --> 01:06:20.230
He kills many friends of the French.

01:06:21.350 --> 01:06:24.610
Which white man is an enemy of France?

01:06:25.230 --> 01:06:26.150
Ask the Delaware chief.

01:06:26.750 --> 01:06:27.390
The scout!

01:06:28.470 --> 01:06:28.830
Hawkeye!

01:06:29.410 --> 01:06:30.010
Said Magua.

01:06:30.390 --> 01:06:31.370
The long gun!

01:06:32.210 --> 01:06:34.590
The other strangers are his friends.

01:06:35.530 --> 01:06:37.670
They are the enemies of France too.

01:06:39.410 --> 01:06:41.750
The Delaware's started to talk quietly.

01:06:42.750 --> 01:06:44.990
One of them left the meeting house quickly.

01:06:46.170 --> 01:06:48.230
A few minutes later, he came back.

01:06:51.000 --> 01:06:54.530
Then a very old man came into the meeting house.

01:06:55.530 --> 01:06:58.330
Two young Delaware's helped the old man.

01:06:59.030 --> 01:07:02.230
He had long white hair and there were many lines

01:07:02.230 --> 01:07:03.270
on his face.

01:07:04.550 --> 01:07:07.510
The chiefs spoke his name, Tamanund.

01:07:08.910 --> 01:07:12.070
Magua knew the name of this famous Delaware chief.

01:07:13.010 --> 01:07:16.250
Tamanund was more than one hundred years old.

01:07:17.610 --> 01:07:19.090
Tamanund sat down.

01:07:20.090 --> 01:07:22.650
Then he spoke to the two young Delaware's.

01:07:23.130 --> 01:07:25.590
They got up and went away.

01:07:26.990 --> 01:07:32.830
Soon they came back with Alice, Cora, Duncan and Hawkeye.

01:07:33.970 --> 01:07:35.610
Cora was very angry.

01:07:36.350 --> 01:07:37.450
She spoke to the chiefs.

01:07:38.490 --> 01:07:42.430
Yesterday we were welcome in this village, she said.

01:07:42.430 --> 01:07:45.310
The Delaware's were our friends.

01:07:46.310 --> 01:07:48.050
Today we are your prisoners.

01:07:49.090 --> 01:07:50.790
Why are we prisoners?

01:07:52.290 --> 01:07:54.170
Tamanund did not answer.

01:07:54.950 --> 01:07:57.290
Which man is Hawkeye?

01:07:58.190 --> 01:07:59.250
The long gun!

01:07:59.770 --> 01:08:00.190
He asked.

01:08:01.270 --> 01:08:02.470
Hawkeye walked forward.

01:08:03.250 --> 01:08:05.670
I am Hawkeye, he said.

01:08:06.670 --> 01:08:08.950
Then Tamanund spoke quickly to Magua.

01:08:08.950 --> 01:08:12.190
Take your prisoner, the dark-haired woman.

01:08:12.790 --> 01:08:13.150
Go!

01:08:13.590 --> 01:08:14.010
He said.

01:08:15.030 --> 01:08:17.450
But Cora spoke to the old chief.

01:08:18.390 --> 01:08:21.130
Another man came to this village with us.

01:08:21.510 --> 01:08:21.850
She said.

01:08:22.490 --> 01:08:24.470
Now he is a prisoner too.

01:08:25.230 --> 01:08:27.450
But he is one of your own people.

01:08:28.330 --> 01:08:29.710
He will tell our story.

01:08:30.550 --> 01:08:32.670
Please listen to him.

01:08:34.150 --> 01:08:35.630
Tamanund looked at the chiefs.

01:08:36.570 --> 01:08:38.970
Who is this other prisoner?

01:08:39.750 --> 01:08:40.090
He asked.

01:08:40.870 --> 01:08:42.390
He fights for the English.

01:08:42.970 --> 01:08:43.730
Magua said quickly.

01:08:44.230 --> 01:08:45.310
You must kill him.

01:08:46.090 --> 01:08:47.630
Bring him here.

01:08:48.170 --> 01:08:48.910
Said Tamanund.

01:08:49.830 --> 01:08:51.650
Two men left the meeting house.

01:08:52.610 --> 01:08:55.770
Soon they came back with Onkas.

01:08:58.890 --> 01:09:01.130
Onkas was not wearing a shirt.

01:09:02.030 --> 01:09:03.410
His hands were tied.

01:09:04.050 --> 01:09:06.110
He stood in front of Tamanund.

01:09:06.850 --> 01:09:08.750
The old chief looked at him.

01:09:09.610 --> 01:09:13.130
Tamanund saw a tattoo on Onkas' chest.

01:09:13.950 --> 01:09:15.630
It was a picture of a turtle.

01:09:16.650 --> 01:09:18.710
Who are you?

01:09:19.390 --> 01:09:20.590
The old chief asked.

01:09:21.550 --> 01:09:24.730
I am Onkas, son of Chingachkuk.

01:09:25.290 --> 01:09:27.610
Son of the great Unamis, the turtle.

01:09:28.310 --> 01:09:28.910
Onkas replied.

01:09:30.010 --> 01:09:32.930
Chingachkuk and Onkas are the last

01:09:32.930 --> 01:09:33.630
of the Mohicans.

01:09:36.790 --> 01:09:38.090
Tamanund looked at Onkas.

01:09:39.010 --> 01:09:41.030
Then he smiled at the young Mohican.

01:09:41.990 --> 01:09:45.250
Your father is a great chief.

01:09:45.930 --> 01:09:46.270
He said.

01:09:47.290 --> 01:09:49.250
Onkas suddenly saw Hawkeye.

01:09:50.270 --> 01:09:52.590
Delaware father, he said to Tamanund.

01:09:53.070 --> 01:09:55.090
This is my friend Hawkeye.

01:09:55.950 --> 01:09:58.430
He is a friend of the Delaware's.

01:09:58.910 --> 01:10:00.550
The long gun?

01:10:00.550 --> 01:10:01.910
Said Tamanund.

01:10:02.590 --> 01:10:05.790
He is not a friend of the Delaware's.

01:10:06.290 --> 01:10:08.550
He kills our young men.

01:10:09.690 --> 01:10:11.410
Then Hawkeye spoke.

01:10:12.090 --> 01:10:14.390
I kill Hurans, he said.

01:10:15.150 --> 01:10:16.830
I have never killed a Delaware.

01:10:18.330 --> 01:10:21.570
The Delaware's believed Hawkeye's words.

01:10:22.870 --> 01:10:24.570
Tamanund looked at Onkas.

01:10:25.250 --> 01:10:28.610
Why are you the Hurans prisoner?

01:10:28.610 --> 01:10:29.690
He asked.

01:10:30.370 --> 01:10:33.730
I helped the English woman, said Onkas.

01:10:34.990 --> 01:10:36.830
Tamanund looked at Cora.

01:10:37.570 --> 01:10:39.450
Then he spoke to Magua.

01:10:40.130 --> 01:10:44.530
And why is the English woman your prisoner?

01:10:45.190 --> 01:10:45.470
He asked.

01:10:46.330 --> 01:10:49.490
I hate the English, said Magua.

01:10:50.110 --> 01:10:54.190
Now the daughter of an English chief is my prisoner.

01:10:54.190 --> 01:10:59.670
Now the daughter of Monroe will be my wife.

01:11:00.830 --> 01:11:03.670
Magua went to Cora and held her arm.

01:11:04.150 --> 01:11:05.670
Wait, shouted Duncan.

01:11:06.210 --> 01:11:06.930
Don't take her.

01:11:07.510 --> 01:11:08.930
The English will give you money.

01:11:10.090 --> 01:11:11.810
But Magua did not listen.

01:11:12.590 --> 01:11:14.450
He pulled Cora towards the door.

01:11:15.350 --> 01:11:16.990
Come, he said to her.

01:11:17.690 --> 01:11:20.470
I am your prisoner, Cora said to Magua.

01:11:20.950 --> 01:11:22.630
But do not touch me.

01:11:23.690 --> 01:11:25.010
She turned to Duncan.

01:11:26.010 --> 01:11:29.310
Please take care of my young sister, she said.

01:11:30.190 --> 01:11:31.210
She kissed Alice.

01:11:32.290 --> 01:11:33.990
Then she spoke to Magua.

01:11:34.850 --> 01:11:36.570
I will come with you.

01:11:37.370 --> 01:11:39.590
And I will come too, shouted Duncan.

01:11:40.110 --> 01:11:41.230
I will help you Cora.

01:11:41.750 --> 01:11:42.910
Wait, said Hawkeye.

01:11:43.470 --> 01:11:44.610
He held Duncan's arm.

01:11:45.470 --> 01:11:47.210
Hawkeye spoke quickly and quietly.

01:11:48.370 --> 01:11:51.670
Magua's friends are waiting in the forest, he said.

01:11:51.670 --> 01:11:53.070
They will kill you.

01:11:53.970 --> 01:11:55.750
You're on, said Onkas.

01:11:56.230 --> 01:11:57.350
We will find you.

01:11:57.890 --> 01:11:59.390
We will kill you.

01:12:00.310 --> 01:12:01.430
But Magua laughed.

01:12:01.990 --> 01:12:04.150
More he can, said Magua.

01:12:04.510 --> 01:12:06.330
You cannot kill me.

01:12:06.970 --> 01:12:08.810
I am too strong.

01:12:09.690 --> 01:12:13.150
Stay here with your brothers, the Delaware's.

01:12:13.590 --> 01:12:14.530
They are weak.

01:12:15.310 --> 01:12:18.570
They like their homes and their food.

01:12:19.520 --> 01:12:21.350
They do not like fighting.

01:12:22.090 --> 01:12:23.830
They will not help you.

01:12:25.350 --> 01:12:28.050
Then Magua walked out of the meeting house.

01:12:29.010 --> 01:12:30.030
Cora followed him.

01:12:31.630 --> 01:12:33.050
Onkas spoke to Tamanund.

01:12:33.630 --> 01:12:36.510
Delaware father, he said, help us.

01:12:37.410 --> 01:12:39.710
We must follow the English woman.

01:12:41.410 --> 01:12:43.930
Tamanund called the young man of the village.

01:12:44.670 --> 01:12:47.410
Go with the Mohican, he said.

01:12:47.410 --> 01:12:51.370
The Eurons are now our enemies.

01:13:06.330 --> 01:13:07.290
Chapter 12.

01:13:08.250 --> 01:13:09.570
The Last of the Mohicans.

01:13:11.770 --> 01:13:15.290
Magua and Cora walked into the forest.

01:13:15.290 --> 01:13:18.470
They walked towards the Eurons village.

01:13:19.630 --> 01:13:25.110
An hour later, Hawkeye, Duncan and Unkas followed Magua's trail.

01:13:26.390 --> 01:13:29.970
Two hundred young Delaware's went with the three friends.

01:13:31.130 --> 01:13:33.270
Alice stayed in the Delaware's village.

01:13:34.790 --> 01:13:36.450
Hawkeye spoke to Unkas.

01:13:37.630 --> 01:13:41.170
Major Hayward and I will find Chingotchkook and General Monroe,

01:13:41.770 --> 01:13:42.090
he said.

01:13:42.790 --> 01:13:44.410
They are safe in the forest.

01:13:45.150 --> 01:13:47.610
Unkas, take the Delaware's with you.

01:13:48.150 --> 01:13:49.550
Follow Magua's trail.

01:13:50.370 --> 01:13:51.270
Be careful.

01:13:52.150 --> 01:13:54.010
There will be many Hurons in the forest.

01:13:54.930 --> 01:13:57.130
We will meet you at the Hurons village.

01:13:58.790 --> 01:14:01.650
Magua will take Cora to the cave in the hill,

01:14:01.930 --> 01:14:02.730
said Hawkeye.

01:14:03.290 --> 01:14:04.290
We will find her.

01:14:05.130 --> 01:14:06.250
We will help her.

01:14:07.170 --> 01:14:08.530
Come, said Duncan.

01:14:11.090 --> 01:14:14.970
Hawkeye and Duncan soon found Chingotchkook and Monroe.

01:14:16.310 --> 01:14:18.090
They quickly told Monroe their story.

01:14:19.210 --> 01:14:21.670
Then the four men went to the Hurons village.

01:14:22.730 --> 01:14:24.970
They walked up the hill towards the cave.

01:14:28.690 --> 01:14:31.030
Suddenly they heard shouts and cries.

01:14:32.430 --> 01:14:33.450
They looked down at the village.

01:14:34.450 --> 01:14:37.470
Unkas and the Delaware's were fighting the Hurons in the

01:14:37.470 --> 01:14:37.710
village.

01:14:38.470 --> 01:14:41.790
Then Magua and some Hurons ran up the hill.

01:14:42.850 --> 01:14:43.870
They were going to the cave.

01:14:44.830 --> 01:14:46.590
Unkas was running after them.

01:14:47.490 --> 01:14:50.090
Hawkeye and his friends fought the Hurons.

01:14:50.770 --> 01:14:53.830
The fight was terrible, but Magua escaped.

01:14:55.270 --> 01:15:00.670
Then Hawkeye, Duncan, Monroe, the Mohicans and their friends saw

01:15:00.670 --> 01:15:01.530
Magua again.

01:15:02.490 --> 01:15:03.890
He was with another Huron.

01:15:04.450 --> 01:15:06.290
They were in front of the cave.

01:15:06.990 --> 01:15:10.530
The two Indians were pulling Cora from the cave.

01:15:11.370 --> 01:15:12.950
Cora, shouted Duncan.

01:15:13.430 --> 01:15:14.310
There is Cora.

01:15:15.190 --> 01:15:18.070
Unkas ran towards the rocks above the cave.

01:15:18.890 --> 01:15:20.910
Cora had stopped in front of the cave.

01:15:21.930 --> 01:15:23.410
Magua took out his knife.

01:15:24.250 --> 01:15:25.290
He turned to Cora.

01:15:25.610 --> 01:15:26.890
Woman, he shouted.

01:15:27.710 --> 01:15:29.750
Will you be the wife of Magua?

01:15:30.310 --> 01:15:31.610
Or will you die?

01:15:32.450 --> 01:15:34.010
Kill me, Magua.

01:15:34.310 --> 01:15:36.930
Cora said, I will not go with you.

01:15:38.090 --> 01:15:39.630
Suddenly there was a crime.

01:15:40.470 --> 01:15:43.030
Unkas was standing on the rocks above them.

01:15:43.850 --> 01:15:44.810
Magua looked up.

01:15:45.750 --> 01:15:47.430
The other Huron turned to Cora.

01:15:48.030 --> 01:15:50.950
He stabbed her with his knife and killed her.

01:15:52.350 --> 01:15:54.010
Magua shouted angrily.

01:15:54.530 --> 01:15:57.050
He lifted his knife and killed the Huron.

01:15:57.590 --> 01:15:59.850
Then Unkas jumped on Magua.

01:15:59.850 --> 01:16:03.230
They fought, but Magua turned quickly.

01:16:03.730 --> 01:16:05.790
He stabbed Unkas four times.

01:16:06.810 --> 01:16:08.610
The young Mohican stood for a moment.

01:16:09.390 --> 01:16:11.330
Then he fell at Magua's feet.

01:16:12.250 --> 01:16:12.790
Dead.

01:16:13.950 --> 01:16:15.630
Hawkeye saw Unkas fall.

01:16:16.510 --> 01:16:18.530
The scout ran towards Magua.

01:16:19.150 --> 01:16:20.630
Magua ran up the path.

01:16:21.650 --> 01:16:22.890
His enemies were below him.

01:16:23.630 --> 01:16:25.090
Magua climbed up the rocks.

01:16:25.970 --> 01:16:27.250
Then he turned and looked down.

01:16:28.130 --> 01:16:29.850
Hawkeye stopped running.

01:16:30.710 --> 01:16:32.390
He lifted his long gun.

01:16:33.430 --> 01:16:37.010
Magua jumped towards a higher rock and Hawkeye fired.

01:16:37.950 --> 01:16:40.290
Magua's fingers touched the rock,

01:16:40.830 --> 01:16:43.910
but the bullet from Hawkeye's gun killed him.

01:16:44.890 --> 01:16:49.350
And his body fell down and down onto the rocks.

01:16:53.310 --> 01:16:58.150
A day later, General Monroe, Duncan, and Alice

01:16:58.150 --> 01:17:01.570
stood by the graves of Unkas and Cora.

01:17:02.290 --> 01:17:03.950
They were sad and silent.

01:17:05.570 --> 01:17:08.410
Then they said goodbye to Hawkeye, Chingachkuk,

01:17:08.870 --> 01:17:09.730
and the Delaware's.

01:17:10.590 --> 01:17:12.510
And they walked away into the forest.

01:17:14.070 --> 01:17:16.030
Chingachkuk looked at Hawkeye.

01:17:17.170 --> 01:17:19.330
All the people of my tribe.

01:17:19.330 --> 01:17:21.710
Have gone now, he said.

01:17:22.430 --> 01:17:24.530
I am alone.

01:17:25.730 --> 01:17:27.490
No, said Hawkeye.

01:17:28.190 --> 01:17:32.650
Unkas has gone, but you are not alone.

01:17:33.850 --> 01:17:36.190
He put his hand on Chingachkuk's hand.

01:17:37.410 --> 01:17:40.950
The tears of the two friends fell onto the grave

01:17:40.950 --> 01:17:42.010
of Unkas.

01:17:48.610 --> 01:17:52.070
In 1758, General Monroe died.

01:17:53.130 --> 01:17:57.110
Alice married Duncan Hayward, and they lived happily together.

01:17:58.270 --> 01:18:01.590
From that time, the Delaware's told their children

01:18:01.590 --> 01:18:05.310
the story of the English woman and the young Mohican.

01:18:06.070 --> 01:18:09.310
And they told their children the words of Tamanun, the

01:18:09.310 --> 01:18:09.810
old chief.

01:18:10.810 --> 01:18:14.990
The time of the Red Man has gone.

01:18:15.930 --> 01:18:21.010
We fought for our land, but now there are many

01:18:21.010 --> 01:18:22.110
white men.

01:18:22.750 --> 01:18:26.370
As many as the leaves on the trees.

01:18:27.650 --> 01:18:30.750
I have lived too long.

01:18:31.730 --> 01:18:36.470
I have seen the last of the Mohicans.

01:18:55.990 --> 01:18:59.890
The last of the Mohicans was read by William Roberts,

01:19:00.430 --> 01:19:03.850
and the recording was produced by James Richardson at Studio

01:19:03.850 --> 01:19:05.290
ADP, London.

01:19:05.290 --> 01:19:10.290
Thank you.

